  "doc_id": "25874",
  "text": "(3) train A random forest model is trained with an equal number of simulation sites and nonmosaic sites. Non-mosaic sites are selected to have equal amounts of heterozygous and homozygous calls in the VCF. We use the RandomForestClassifier module from the scikit-learn library [CITATION_1] with max_leaf_nodes 50 and n_estimators 100, though Samovar allows the user to customize these hyperparameters. The random forest features described in Table S5 take into account the abundance and consistency of evidence for a mosaic variant, including the number of haplotype discordant reads, mosaic allele fraction, base quality, alignment score, amount of soft clipping, presence of indels, etc.",
  "correct_citation": {
